This is our review and benchmark of the NVIDIA GeForce RTX 5060 Ti 16GB GPU, so at least you'll have numbers if this situation ever becomes sane again. Right now though, we just don't see where you buy a card unless truly in need as the pricing situation is out of control across all tiers, used and new alike. We benchmarked the RTX 5060 Ti vs. the RTX 4060 Ti 8GB, the RTX 3070 Ti, 3080, RX 9070, RX 7600, and dozens more video cards to test the performance of something that will ultimately be leveraged by parasites.

This news episode focuses on Nintendo's Switch 2 specs (that we have so far, anyway), games, game prices, and more. We also talk tariffs and the impact on the hardware industry, plus hardware company responses. AMD's RX 9070 GRE has been seen in rumors and the RX 9060 XT popped-up in Korea, with NVIDIA open sourcing more of its PhysX code as a positive story.
